{
  "info": {
    "name": "Linus Health Public API",
    "description": "Linus Health Public API — create subjects, enroll them in campaigns, and retrieve reports.\n\nUsage:\n1. Select the \"Linus Health — Sandbox\" environment and fill in `clientId` / `clientSecret`.\n2. Run any request — a collection-level pre-request script fetches and caches a Bearer token automatically (or run \"OAuth Token\" explicitly).\n3. \"Register Subject\" saves `participantId`; \"Enroll Subject\" saves `enrollmentId` and logs the `redirect` link.\n\nDocs: docs/linus/Linus Health Public API.pdf",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{bearerToken}}", "type": "string" }]
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Auto-refresh the Bearer token for every request except the token call itself.",
          "if (pm.info.requestName === 'OAuth Token') { return; }",
          "",
          "const token = pm.collectionVariables.get('bearerToken');",
          "const expiresAt = Number(pm.collectionVariables.get('tokenExpiresAt') || 0);",
          "// Reuse a cached token until 60s before expiry.",
          "if (token && Date.now() < expiresAt - 60000) { return; }",
          "",
          "pm.sendRequest({",
          "  url: pm.environment.get('tokenUrl'),",
          "  method: 'POST',",
          "  header: { 'Content-Type': 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded' },",
          "  body: {",
          "    mode: 'urlencoded',",
          "    urlencoded: [",
          "      { key: 'grant_type', value: 'client_credentials' },",
          "      { key: 'client_id', value: pm.environment.get('clientId') },",
          "      { key: 'client_secret', value: pm.environment.get('clientSecret') },",
          "      { key: 'audience', value: pm.environment.get('audience') }",
          "    ]",
          "  }",
          "}, (err, res) => {",
          "  if (err || res.code !== 200) { console.error('[linus] token error', err || res.text()); return; }",
          "  const data = res.json();",
          "  pm.collectionVariables.set('bearerToken', data.access_token);",
          "  pm.collectionVariables.set('tokenExpiresAt', String(Date.now() + (data.expires_in || 0) * 1000));",
          "});"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "variable": [
    { "key": "bearerToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "tokenExpiresAt", "value": "0" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "OAuth Token",
      "request": {
        "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "urlencoded",
          "urlencoded": [
            { "key": "grant_type", "value": "client_credentials" },
            { "key": "client_id", "value": "{{clientId}}" },
            { "key": "client_secret", "value": "{{clientSecret}}" },
            { "key": "audience", "value": "{{audience}}" }
          ]
        },
        "url": { "raw": "{{tokenUrl}}", "host": ["{{tokenUrl}}"] },
        "description": "OAuth2 client-credentials grant. Returns a short-lived Bearer token. The test script caches it for the other requests."
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
              "  const data = pm.response.json();",
              "  pm.collectionVariables.set('bearerToken', data.access_token);",
              "  pm.collectionVariables.set('tokenExpiresAt', String(Date.now() + (data.expires_in || 0) * 1000));",
              "  console.log('[linus] token acquired, expires_in =', data.expires_in);",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "List Campaigns",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [{ "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/campaigns",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["campaigns"]
        },
        "description": "GET /v1/campaigns — returns all available campaigns ({ items: [{ campaignId, name }] })."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Get Campaign by ID",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [{ "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/campaigns/{{campaignId}}",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["campaigns", "{{campaignId}}"]
        },
        "description": "GET /v1/campaigns/{campaignId} — returns a single campaign ({ campaignId, name })."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Register Subject",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
          { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"firstName\": \"Test\",\n  \"lastName\": \"Subject\",\n  \"email\": \"test.subject@example.com\",\n  \"sexAssignedAtBirth\": \"FEMALE\",\n  \"races\": [\"WHITE\"],\n  \"ethnicity\": \"NOT_HISPANIC_OR_LATINO\",\n  \"education\": \"ED_YEARS_16\",\n  \"ageIndicator\": { \"birthDate\": \"1970-01-01\" },\n  \"consent\": true\n}",
          "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/participants",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["participants"]
        },
        "description": "POST /v1/participants — register a subject. Saves the returned `participantId` for the requests below.\n\n`sexAssignedAtBirth` (required): MALE | FEMALE | INTERSEX | OTHER. `ageIndicator` (required): one of { birthDate: \"YYYY-MM-DD\" } | { birthYear } | { yearsOld } (birthDate required for healthcare use). `races`, `ethnicity`, `education` (ED_YEARS_*), `externalId` are optional."
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "if (pm.response.code >= 200 && pm.response.code < 300) {",
              "  const data = pm.response.json();",
              "  if (data.participantId) {",
              "    pm.environment.set('participantId', data.participantId);",
              "    console.log('[linus] participantId =', data.participantId);",
              "  }",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Get Subject by ID",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [{ "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/participants/{{participantId}}",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["participants", "{{participantId}}"]
        },
        "description": "GET /v1/participants/{participantId} — returns the details of a subject."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Enroll Subject",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
          { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"participantId\": \"{{participantId}}\",\n  \"campaignId\": \"{{campaignId}}\",\n  \"consent\": true\n}",
          "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/participants/{{participantId}}/enrollments",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["participants", "{{participantId}}", "enrollments"]
        },
        "description": "POST /v1/participants/{id}/enrollments — enroll the subject in a campaign. Idempotent: only one enrollment per campaign can be active at a time; if one already exists, that active enrollment is returned. Saves `enrollmentId` and logs the subject `redirect` link.\n\nSet `campaignId` from a sandbox campaign (campaignId_LHQ / campaignId_ePSOM / campaignId_DAC are in the environment)."
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "if (pm.response.code >= 200 && pm.response.code < 300) {",
              "  const data = pm.response.json();",
              "  if (data.enrollmentId) { pm.environment.set('enrollmentId', data.enrollmentId); }",
              "  if (data.redirect) { console.log('[linus] redirect =', data.redirect); }",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "List Enrollments",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [{ "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/participants/{{participantId}}/enrollments",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["participants", "{{participantId}}", "enrollments"]
        },
        "description": "GET /v1/participants/{id}/enrollments — list the subject's active (not-yet-completed) enrollments and their redirect links. Read-only."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Get Report",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [{ "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/participants/{{participantId}}/enrollments/{{enrollmentId}}/reports/{{reportType}}",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": [
            "participants",
            "{{participantId}}",
            "enrollments",
            "{{enrollmentId}}",
            "reports",
            "{{reportType}}"
          ]
        },
        "description": "GET /v1/participants/{id}/enrollments/{enrollmentId}/reports/{reportType} — retrieve a results report (base64-encoded/serialized PDF). `reportType` is patient-report | provider-report. Reports only exist once the subject finishes the assessment, and not all campaigns support all report types."
      }
    }
  ]
}
